CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 16, 1952, pg. 5, reads: "Wins Frogs Purse - 'Passing Parade,' owned by Mrs. D. S. Winchester, trained by N. Corbin and ridden by Jockey W. Young, won the 'Frogs' Purse,' $1,500 feature race, at Wheeling Downs last Wednesday. The rave was named in honor of the Frogs Club, which was celebrating Frog Week.'  Left to right, unidentified stable boy; Corbin, Dr. Woodford (Woody) Harris, chairman of the derby trek, and Dr. Charles Cephas, president of the Frogs who presented the trophy to the owners of the horse winning the race. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of seven men, including jockey W. Young, seated on horse "Passing Parade," trainer N. Corbin wearing hat, Dr. Woodford "Woody" Harris, and Dr. Charles Cephas holding trophy, posed on track in Wheeling Downs for FROGS race
